lexicon: {'brief': 'Gehenna', 'long': 'Gehenna, and originally the name of a valley or cavity near Jerusalem, a place underneath the earth, a place of punishment for evil.'}

{'brief': 'eternal, unending', 'long': 'age-long, and therefore: practically eternal, unending; partaking of the character of that which lasts for an age, as contrasted with that which is brief and fleeting.'}
{'brief': 'I choose, prefer', 'long': 'I choose, prefer.'}

{'brief': 'profane, secular, unspiritual, godless, worldly', 'long': 'permitted to be trodden, accessible.'}

{'brief': 'the baptizer, the Baptist', 'long': 'the baptizer, the Baptist, epithet used only of John, the son of Zechariah and Elizabeth, forerunner of Jesus.'}

{'brief': 'I will, intend, desire', 'long': 'I will, intend, desire, wish.'}

{'brief': 'justice, judicial hearing, punishment', 'long': '(a) (originally: custom, usage) right, justice, (b) process of law, judicial hearing, (c) execution of sentence, punishment, penalty, (d) justice, vengeance.'}

{'brief': 'a mandate, decree', 'long': 'a mandate, decree, edict.'}

{'brief': 'acquittal, justification', 'long': 'acquittal, justifying, justification, a process of absolution.'}

{'brief': 'justice, justness, righteousness', 'long': '(usually if not always in a Jewish atmosphere), justice, justness, righteousness, righteousness of which God is the source or author, but practically: a divine righteousness.'}

{'brief': 'a judge', 'long': 'a judge.'}

{'brief': 'service, worship', 'long': 'service rendered to God, perhaps simply: worship.'}

{'brief': 'a people, the crowd', 'long': "(a) a people, characteristically of God's chosen people, first the Jews, then the Christians, (b) sometimes, but rarely, the people, the crowd."}

{'brief': 'I minister, serve publicly', 'long': 'I act in the public service, render service, minister, in the widest sense, of some special public religious service, but also of the service of priests and Levites.'}
{'brief': 'a charitable gift, public service', 'long': 'a charitable gift, public service in the widest sense; service as of priest or Levite ritual.'}
{'brief': 'ministering', 'long': 'given to serving (ministration), ministering.'}

{'brief': 'I stone, cast stones at', 'long': 'I stone, cast stones (at), kill by stoning.'}
